ext.Context) {\n    cachePath := k.sessionIDCachePath(ctx)\n    if err := os.Remove(cachePath); err != nil && !os.IsNotExist(err) {\n        logging.Warn(ctx, \"kiro: failed to clear session ID cache\", \"err\", err)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/lifecycle.go`\n- Add `clearCachedSessionID` method\n- Call it at end of `parseStop` (after line 174, before the return)\n- Add test: `TestSessionIDCaching_StopClearsCache` — verify cache file is removed after stop\n\n### 2. Fix capture.json format in test script\n\n**Bug:** `scripts/test-kiro-agent-integration.sh` writes hooks at top-level of `capture.json`, but Kiro expects `kiroAgentFile` format with `name`, `tools`, and `hooks` nesting.\n\n**Fix:** Wrap the hooks in the correct structure:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"capture\",\n  \"tools\": [\"shell\"],\n  \"hooks\": {\n    \"agentSpawn\": [{\"command\": \"cat > ...\"}],\n    \"userPromptSubmit\": [{\"command\": \"cat > ...\"}],\n    \"stop\": [{\"command\": \"cat > ...\"}]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**File:** `scripts/test-kiro-agent-integration.sh` (lines 53-59)\n\n---\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\n```\n\nThe new `TestSessionIDCaching_StopClearsCache` test will verify the cache clearing behavior.\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/alisha/.claude/projects/-Users-alisha-Projects-wt-kiro-oneshot/7d500980-585e-442f-839d-e2308b5d8e1f.jsonl\n\n---\n\ncommit"